# Semicolon Style

Avoid semicolons in JavaScript/TypeScript code. Only use them when strictly necessary to prevent Automatic Semicolon Insertion (ASI) issues, such as:

- Lines starting with `(`, `[`, `/`, `+`, `-`, or a template literal
- IIFE expressions

**Good:**
```typescript
const foo = "bar"
const arr = [1, 2, 3]
function greet() {
  console.log("hello")
}
```

**Bad:**
```typescript
const foo = "bar";
const arr = [1, 2, 3];
function greet() {
  console.log("hello");
}
```